      "content": "<objective>\nClarify phase P41-A requirements through structured analysis with ambiguity scoring.\nProduce SPEC.md in `.planning/phases/P41-state-cluster-redesign/` with falsifiable requirements.\n\n**Position in workflow:** spec-phase → research → plan → check → execute\n\n**Phase:** P41-A\n**Mode:** --auto (skip interactive, use recommended defaults)\n\n## Phase Context\n\n**P41-A: Investigate Field Mapping + Affected Tools for State Cluster Consolidation**\n\nThe user decided to MERGE delegations.json + session-continuity.json data into session-tracker per-session files, then DELETE the 2 standalone files. Rationale:\n- Both files contain ZERO real production data (all test artifacts)\n- They grow unbounded (accumulate all delegations/sessions in one file)\n- No progressive disclosure mechanism for agents to read them\n- Session-tracker already tracks 117 real sessions with per-session files (correct pattern)\n\n**This investigation phase must determine:**\n1. What unique fields exist in delegations.json that session-tracker doesn't have?\n2. What unique fields exist in session-continuity.json that session-tracker doesn't have?\n3. Where does each unique field map in session-tracker's per-session schema?\n4. What tools/agents/hooks read or write each field?\n5. What would break if we remove the 2 files?\n\n## Key Decision Already Locked\n- MERGE into session-tracker, DELETE both files (user confirmed)\n- This phase is INVESTIGATION only — no file modifications\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. **Scout codebase** — Read the relevant source files to understand current state\n2. **Read phase context** — ROADMAP.md, trajectory-ledger for context\n3. **Define requirements** — Falsifiable, bounded, measurable\n4. **Score ambiguity** — Target ≤ 0.20\n5. **Write SPEC.md** to `.planning/phases/P41-state-cluster-redesign/P41-A-SPEC.md`\n\n## Output Format\n\nWrite SPEC.md with these sections:\n1. **Requirements** — falsifiable numbered list (REQ-P41A-01 through REQ-P41A-N)\n2. **Boundaries** — what's IN scope, what's OUT of scope\n3. **Actors** — which tools/agents/hooks are affected\n4. **Acceptance Criteria** — how we verify this investigation is complete\n5. **Ambiguity Score** — final score and dimension breakdown\n\nReturn the FULL content of what you wrote.",
